Export sq objects into other formats

Source: R/export_sq.R
export_sq.Rd

Convert object of class sq to another class from another package. Currently supported packages are ape with its formats (AAbin and DNAbin), Bioconductor (AAStringSet, DNAStringSet) and seqinr (SeqFastaAA, SeqFastadna).

export_sq(sq, export_format, name)

Arguments

sq

a sq object.
export_format

a character string indicating package and the destination class; it should be one of the following: "seqinr::SeqFastaAA", "ape::AAbin", "Biostrings::AAStringSet", "seqinr::SeqFastadna", "ape::DNAbin", "Biostrings::DNAStringSet".
name

a character vector of length equal to sq length.

See also

sq import_sq

Examples

sq_ami <- construct_sq(c("MVVGL", "LAVPP"))
export_sq(sq_ami, "ape::AAbin")
#> 2 amino acid sequences in a list
#> 
#> All sequences of the same length: 5 
#> 
export_sq(sq_ami, "Biostrings::AAStringSet", c("one", "two"))
#>   A AAStringSet instance of length 2
#>     width seq                                               names               
#> [1]     5 MVVGL                                             one
#> [2]     5 LAVPP                                             two
export_sq(sq_ami, "seqinr::SeqFastaAA")
#> [[1]]
#> [1] "M" "V" "V" "G" "L"
#> attr(,"class")
#> [1] "SeqFastaAA"
#> 
#> [[2]]
#> [1] "L" "A" "V" "P" "P"
#> attr(,"class")
#> [1] "SeqFastaAA"
#> 

sq_nuc <- construct_sq(c("TGATGAAGCGCA", "TTGATGGGAA"))
export_sq(sq_nuc, "ape::DNAbin", name = c("one", "two"))
#> 2 DNA sequences in binary format stored in a list.
#> 
#> Mean sequence length: 11 
#>    Shortest sequence: 10 
#>     Longest sequence: 12 
#> 
#> Labels:
#> one
#> two
#> 
#> Base composition:
#>     a     c     g     t 
#> 0.318 0.091 0.364 0.227 
#> (Total: 22 bases)
export_sq(sq_nuc, "Biostrings::DNAStringSet")
#>   A DNAStringSet instance of length 2
#>     width seq
#> [1]    12 TGATGAAGCGCA
#> [2]    10 TTGATGGGAA
export_sq(sq_nuc, "seqinr::SeqFastadna")
#> [[1]]
#>  [1] "T" "G" "A" "T" "G" "A" "A" "G" "C" "G" "C" "A"
#> attr(,"class")
#> [1] "SeqFastadna"
#> 
#> [[2]]
#>  [1] "T" "T" "G" "A" "T" "G" "G" "G" "A" "A"
#> attr(,"class")
#> [1] "SeqFastadna"
#>
